The paper proposes a framework for analyzing generalization in reinforcement learning, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper also focuses on tool use, which is a behavior observed in animals and humans, suggesting a potential connection to robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of reinforcement learning and generalization also suggests a potential connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Overall, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, and cs.NE.
